review_blob: A strong Beer with a light character and lots of flavour. It was surprisingly easily drunk and was quite bitter. Quite enjoyable.
A blonde tasteful Beer that is quite easily drunk but with lots of flavour. A good Beer if you want something light but flavoursome.
A refreshening Belgian whitbier that is easily drunk and really good as hydration to a quite mild meal.
A sweet Lambic Beer with cherry flavour. Good as a refreshener for a sweet-tooth when thirsty on a hot Sumer day. A solid Beer.
A great Beer to drink after a good meal or if you want a complex Beer for a quite cheat price. It's dark and complex with flavours that will stay in your mouth for a while.
This Trappist Beer was drunk at a pub called Man in the Moon in Stockholm, Rdmansgatan. I must say that it is one of the best Beers that I've drunk. Much flavour but easy to drink. Worth every Penny!
